Dream Knights publishes a ready to play, full system LARP handbook.<br>
LARP, the cornerstone of our programs is our unique mythical game in which players enter a magical world. Participants act out many roles, becoming heroines, magicians, faeries, healers, sages, warriors, and more. <br>
<br>
Our normal adventure modules are for single players, groups of 6-10 players, all of who will be at a similar level of character development. Don't worry if you are not part of a group, as we will arrange for others in a similar position to adventure with you. <br>
 <br>
NEW:  LARP Adventures indoor modules.<br>
<br>
-Come LARP every Saturday and Sunday.  A different adventure module every week. Fight your way through the mazes, try to open locked doors as your fighters keep the enemy at bay, and more! With your LARP weapons you will have to fight your way through the adventure module.  It is playing in a LARP every week!  Develop your character and earn skills!<br>
<br>
-Pre-register personal modules at all times.<br>
<br>
Whole weekend overland adventures are also run for more experienced players.<br>
Each year Dream Knights runs a number of weekend adventures, during which the players remain in-character and role-playing for 24 hours a day, throughout the whole 3 days of the game.  This grueling experience is considered by most to be the peak of live role-playing, giving participants the chance to get more deeply into character than in any other game.  This year the Dream Knights are running twelve such weekends.<br>
However, be warned that these adventures usually fill up with our dedicated players within a week or two of opening booking procedures, so it is very important to pre-register.<br>
<br>
 Fight Club-Televised Fantasy Fight Club<br>
Compete in Fantasy Martial Arts Tournament to win in-game treasure &amp; prizes!<br>
Discounts to Weekend events available.<br>
<br>
Saturday and Sundays at 9:30Am-10:30pm.<br>
Six modules per day.<br>
Minimum six players per module.<br>
Cost: $15 per module. ( Pre-registration only. ) <br>
$15 Taverning. ( Open role-playing in the tavern. Fantasy Fight Club. )<br>
Download the roolbook at –www.dreamknights.com<br>
Earned Build: 1 per Day.<br>
<br>
<br>
DREAMTV <br>
WEB/CABLE TV SHOW  <br>
<br>
<br>
The Dream Knights LARP is in the production of a full length fantasy based movie and Documentary on Live Action Role-playing. The main characters stories and shots will be taken from our monthly game and production of a WEB/CABLE TV show.<br>
 <br>
The main characters for the TV show will be chosen from the most interesting player characters.  <br>
The players will determine the storyline just by participating in the monthly game.  The best role-playing/acting performances will be the ones that the show will focus on.  However, this does not mean by simply being a player you would not have the opportunity for a part in the monthly show or the full-length end production.<br>
<br>
The following are non-paying non-union potions:<br>
2 News Hosts. (News show format)<br>
